1 olive oil
1 packet Crumbed Chicken Breast Strips
1 tomato
½ head cos lettuce
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet garlic aioli

In a large frying pan, heat a generous drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook crumbed chicken breast strips until golden and cooked through, 3-4 minutes each side. Season, slice and set aside.

While chicken is cooking, thinly slice tomato into half-moons. Roughly chop cos lettuce (see ingredients).

Spread garlic aioli over mini flour tortillas. Top with tomato, chicken and cos lettuce. Tuck in ends of tortillas and roll into wraps. Wrap in foil or plastic wrap. Refrigerate until ready to serve.